# 🏗️ Technical Architecture

## Stack Decisions

| Component | Decision | Why |
|-----------|----------|-----|
| **App shell** | SvelteKit 2 | Write-heavy offline PWA; Astro's MPA routing fights offline UX |
| **Content site** | Astro | Species guides, docs, blog — static content hydration is perfect |
| **Mobile wrapper** | Capacitor (iOS v1.2) | Escape WebKit ITP eviction; reuse PWA codebase |
| **Offline sync** | Dexie IndexedDB outbox + REST | Append-heavy, single-author; CRDTs overkill |
| **Offline maps** | MapLibre GL JS + pmtiles on R2 | Mapbox GL JS has no offline web support |
| **On-device ML** | EfficientNet-Lite0 INT8 ONNX | Sub-3MB bundle; WebGPU → WASM fallback |
| **Vision API** | Gemini Flash-Lite → Haiku 4.5 | Cost-optimized routing; Sonnet only for expert review |
| **Audio AI** | BirdNET (commercial license) | Best open acoustic model; ⚠️ weights are CC BY-NC-SA |
| **Storage** | Cloudflare R2 | Zero egress fees — $150/mo vs $4,710/mo Supabase Storage at 10K MAU |
| **Database** | PostGIS + pgvector + Supabase | Geography type, GIST, pg_partman monthly partitions |
| **Data residency** | AWS mx-central-1 option | LGPDPPSO compliance for B2G Mexican clients |

> ⚠️ **BirdNET critical:** Model weights are CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 — non-commercial. Source code is MIT but weights are not. Contact ccb-birdnet@cornell.edu for a commercial license before adding any paid tier.

## AI Identification Pipeline

<pre><code>
User uploads media
        |
        v
  Client-side EXIF extraction (exifr) --&gt; GPS, timestamp, device
        |
        v
  Pre-ID quality check --&gt; blur/dark warning
        |
        |--- Plant detected? ---------------&gt; PlantNet Pro API
        |                                      (78K species, confidence)
        |
        |--- Bird sound? ------------------&gt; BirdNET
        |                                      (commercial license)
        |
        +--- General image/video ----------&gt; Gemini 2.5 Flash-Lite
                                              |
                                              +- conf &gt;= 0.8 --&gt; Result
                                              |
                                              +- conf &lt; 0.8 --&gt; Claude Haiku 4.5
                                                                 |
                                                                 +- conf &gt;= 0.7 --&gt; Result
                                                                 |
                                                                 +- Expert queue --&gt; Sonnet

Offline fallback:
  EfficientNet-Lite0 INT8 ONNX (&lt;3MB, top 500 species)
  + Regional packs (Oaxaca/Yucatan 10-30MB, lazy-loaded into IndexedDB)
</code></pre>

## Cost Model

| Scale | Monthly cost | Per-user |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| 10K MAU | ~$2,000 | $0.20 |
| 50K MAU | ~$6,000 | $0.12 |
| 100K MAU | ~$11,500 | $0.12 |

*Includes: Supabase Pro + R2 + ~500K Claude Haiku calls + 600K PlantNet Pro + Gemini first-pass + monitoring*

**Freemium model:** 10 IDs/day free · $5/mo unlimited + expert review · $200–2,000/mo institutional

## Database Schema (core tables)

```sql
-- Core observation
observations (
  id uuid PK,
  observer_id uuid FK users,
  observed_at timestamptz,
  location geography(Point, 4326),    -- PostGIS geography
  location_obscured geography(Point), -- public-readable, fuzzy
  habitat_type varchar,
  -- Environmental auto-enrichment
  moon_phase varchar, moon_illumination float,
  precipitation_24h_mm float, ndvi_value float,
  -- EXIF extracted
  captured_at timestamptz, device_make varchar,
  -- Partitioned monthly via pg_partman
)

-- AI identifications
identifications (
  id uuid PK,
  observation_id uuid FK,
  taxon_id uuid FK,
  confidence float,
  source varchar,  -- 'plantnet'|'birdnet'|'claude_haiku'|'human'
  validated_by uuid FK users,
  is_research_grade boolean
)

-- Sensitive location RLS
-- location: auth.uid() = observer_id OR is_credentialed_researcher()
-- location_obscured: public readable (obscure_point() IMMUTABLE function)
```

## iOS PWA Constraints

iOS Safari will kill your PWA if you ignore these:

| Constraint | Mitigation |
|-----------|-----------|
| 7-day ITP storage eviction | `navigator.storage.persist()` on install |
| ~50MB cache soft limit | Keep initial cache under 30MB; lazy-load regional packs |
| No Background Sync API | Flush queue on every app open |
| Web Push requires A2HS | Prompt aggressively for Add-to-Home-Screen |
| WebGPU only Safari 26+ | WASM fallback in ONNX Runtime Web |
| EU DMA breaks Web Push (iOS 17.4) | Capacitor wrapper by v1.2 |

## Offline Maps

```
Zoom 0–10: ~250MB overview (Mexico, pre-bundled)
Zoom 11–14: user downloads 50km radius chunks (~20–60MB each)
           → stored in Dexie blob storage

Stack: MapLibre GL JS + protomaps pmtiles format
       Self-hosted on Cloudflare R2 (zero egress)
```

